---
title: Shrimp Farfalle (AKA Butterfly Pasta) with Bell Pepper, Lemon, and Crispy Breadcrumbs
description: Farfalle pasta is named for the butterflies it resembles. Which is appropriate for this citrusy, summery recipe that’ll make your taste buds flutter and float and feel like they’re on cloud nine. The pasta is mixed with plump shrimp, sweet bell peppers, and fragrant basil, but what really pushes it into sublime territory is the heap of buttery golden breadcrumbs on top that give it a special crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/shrimp-farfalle-aka-butterfly-pasta-e113882b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/shrimp-farfalle-aka-butterfly-pasta-422de3c0.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 78 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shrimp-farfalle-aka-butterfly-pasta-590c7d44c9fd08656a287d12
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Zest @lemon{1} until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into halves. Cut one half into wedges. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Thinly slice @basil{1/2%oz}. Core, seed, and thinly slice @red bell pepper{2}.

Toss bell peppers on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until lightly browned, about ~{15%minutes}.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} and toast, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Once water is boiling, add @farfalle pasta{12%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just al dente, about ~{9%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve 1 cup pasta water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Rinse @shrimp{20%oz} and pat dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with @Italian seasoning{2%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Add to pan and cook, tossing, until almost opaque, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add garlic and cook, tossing, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute} more.

Toss pasta and bell peppers into pan with shrimp. Add lemon zest, @butter{2%tbsp}, half the basil, pasta water, and a squeeze of lemon. Bring to a boil and let bubble, stirring occasionally, until a sauce has formed, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lemon (to taste).

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with panko and remaining basil. Top with a large drizzle of olive oil and serve with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.

> Farfalle pasta is named for the butterflies it resembles - appropriate for this citrusy, summery recipe that makes your taste buds flutter.

> The heap of buttery golden breadcrumbs on top gives this dish a special crunch.